Module kivakit.configuration
Package com.telenav.kivakit.configuration.settings

Interface SettingsTrait

All Known Subinterfaces:
Component, ComponentFunction<From,​To>, ComponentMixin, ComponentSupplier<Value>
All Known Implementing Classes:
Application, BaseComponent, Deployment, Server, Settings, SettingsFolder, SettingsPackage
public interface SettingsTrait

A stateless trait for accessing the Settings for the implementing component. Includes methods to look up, register and require settings objects. When there is more than one settings object of a given type, an InstanceIdentifier can be given to distinguish between instances. Convenience methods are provided to create instance identifiers for Enums and Strings. The Component interface in kivakit-component uses this trait to add easy access to registry methods to all components.

Lookup methods

  • settingsRegistry() - The Settings for this object
  • hasSettings(Class) - Determines if the registered instance of the given class can be found
  • hasSettings(Class, String) - Determines if the registered instance of the given class can be found
  • hasSettings(Class, Enum) - Determines if the registered instance of the given class can be found
  • lookupSettings(Class) - Locates the registered instance of the given class
  • lookupSettings(Class, String) - Locates the specified registered instance of the given class
  • lookupSettings(Class, Enum) - Locates the specified registered instance of the given class

Register methods

  • registerSettings(Object) - Registers the given object
  • registerSettings(Object, String) - Registers the given identified object instance
  • registerSettings(Object, Enum) - Registers the given identified object instance
  • registerAllSettingsIn(Settings) - Registers the settings in the given object with this settings object
  • registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, Folder) - Registers the settings in the given folder with this settings object
  • registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, PackagePath) - Registers the settings in the given package with this settings object
  • registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, Package) - Registers the settings in the given package with this settings object
  • registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, Class) - Registers the settings in the given class' package with this settings object
  • registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, Class, String) - Registers the settings in the given class-relative package with this settings object

Require methods

  • requireSettings(Class) - Locates the registered instance of the given class or fails
  • requireSettings(Class, String) - Locates the specified registered instance of the given class or fails
  • requireSettings(Class, Enum) - Locates the specified registered instance of the given class or fails
